   TestCase Name: heur_rollback_bmt

   Test Category: JCA Heuristic Transactions

   Test Description:
    In this test, the global transaction is failed during the commit phase.
    Due to the order that WAS commits global transactions, branch 2 will not be
    committed.

    Branch 1 = ima.evilra
    Branch 2 = reply message

    Since this is a bean-managed transaction, the message sent to the MDB is not
    a part of the transaction.

    This means that when we heuristically rollback branch 2 of the transaction, we
    are going to maintain the transactional integrity of this global transaction.

    The reply message will be rolled back, and the message originally published
    to the MDB will be published again as that message was never acknowledged.

    This can be seen in the series of "imaserver stat Subscription" output below.

   Before rollback:
     "logSubBMT","/log/Topic","heur_rollback_bmt","True",0,0,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"False",0
     "replyDurableSubBMT","/reply/Topic/DurableBMTUT","heur_rollback_bmt","True",1,1,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"False",0
     "durableBMTUTsub","/send/Topic/DurableBMTUT","__Shared","True",1,1,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"True",0

   After commit:
     "logSubBMT","/log/Topic","heur_rollback_bmt","True",0,0,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"False",0
     "replyDurableSubBMT","/reply/Topic/DurableBMTUT","heur_rollback_bmt","True",0,1,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"False",0
     "durableBMTUTsub","/send/Topic/DurableBMTUT","__Shared","True",1,1,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"True",0

   After WAS restart:
     "logSubBMT","/log/Topic","heur_rollback_bmt","True",1,1,0.0,20000000,1,0,0.0,"False",0
     "replyDurableSubBMT","/reply/Topic/DurableBMTUT","heur_rollback_bmt","True",1,1,0.0,20000000,1,0,0.0,"False",0
     "durableBMTUTsub","/send/Topic/DurableBMTUT","__Shared","True",0,1,0.0,20000000,0,0,0.0,"True",1

  -->
